					<h1 class="pagetitle fn">Pumpkin Cheesecake with Pecan Praline Sauce</h1>
					<div class="postmeta"><a href="https://www.davidlebovitz.com/pumpkin-cheesecake-pecan-praline-sauce-recipe/#comments">75 comments</a> - <time class="entry-date" datetime="2024-11-16T21:56:52+01:00" pubdate content="11-16-2024">11.16.2024</time></div>
				</header>

				<div class="content notop nobot">

					<div class="swp_social_panel swp_horizontal_panel swp_flat_fresh  swp_default_full_color swp_other_full_color swp_individual_full_color scale-100 scale-full_width" data-min-width="1100" data-float-color="#ffffff" data-float="none" data-float-mobile="none" data-transition="slide" data-post-id="38344" ><div class="nc_tweetContainer swp_share_button swp_pinterest" data-network="pinterest"><a rel="nofollow noreferrer noopener" class="nc_tweet swp_share_link" data-count="0" data-link="https://pinterest.com/pin/create/button/?url=https://www.davidlebovitz.com/pumpkin-cheesecake-pecan-praline-sauce-recipe/&media=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.davidlebovitz.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F01%2FCopy-of-Pumpkin-Cheesecake-with-Pecan-Praline-Sauce-2.png&description=Pumpkin+Cheesecake+with+Pecan+Praline+Sauce+-+a+perfect+holiday+dessert%21+via+%40davidlebovitz" href="https://pinterest.com/pin/create/button/?url=https://www.davidlebovitz.com/pumpkin-cheesecake-pecan-praline-sauce-recipe/&media=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.davidlebovitz.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F01%2FCopy-of-Pumpkin-Cheesecake-with-Pecan-Praline-Sauce-2.png&description=Pumpkin+Cheesecake+with+Pecan+Praline+Sauce+-+a+perfect+holiday+dessert%21+via+%40davidlebovitz" ><span class="iconFiller"><span class="spaceManWilly"><i class="sw swp_pinterest_icon"></i><span class="swp_share">Pin</span></span></span><span class="swp_count">1K</span></a></div><div class="nc_tweetContainer swp_share_button swp_facebook" data-network="facebook"><a class="nc_tweet swp_share_link" rel="nofollow noreferrer noopener" target="_blank" href="https://www.facebook.com/share.php?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.davidlebovitz.com%2Fpumpkin-cheesecake-pecan-praline-sauce-recipe%2F" data-link="https://www.facebook.com/share.php?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.davidlebovitz.com%2Fpumpkin-cheesecake-pecan-praline-sauce-recipe%2F"><span class="swp_count swp_hide"><span class="iconFiller"><span class="spaceManWilly"><i class="sw swp_facebook_icon"></i><span class="swp_share">Share</span></span></span></span></a></div><div class="nc_tweetContainer swp_share_button total_shares total_sharesalt" ><span class="swp_count ">1K <span class="swp_label">Shares</span></span></div></div><p><img fetchpriority="high" decoding="async" class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-38351" src="https://www.davidlebovitz.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Pumpkin-cheesecake-recipe-with-toffee-pecan-sauce_-8-640x921.jpg" alt="" width="640" height="921" srcset="https://www.davidlebovitz.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Pumpkin-cheesecake-recipe-with-toffee-pecan-sauce_-8-640x921.jpg 640w, https://www.davidlebovitz.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Pumpkin-cheesecake-recipe-with-toffee-pecan-sauce_-8-209x300.jpg 209w, https://www.davidlebovitz.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Pumpkin-cheesecake-recipe-with-toffee-pecan-sauce_-8-768x1105.jpg 768w, https://www.davidlebovitz.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Pumpkin-cheesecake-recipe-with-toffee-pecan-sauce_-8-150x216.jpg 150w, https://www.davidlebovitz.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Pumpkin-cheesecake-recipe-with-toffee-pecan-sauce_-8-600x863.jpg 600w, https://www.davidlebovitz.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Pumpkin-cheesecake-recipe-with-toffee-pecan-sauce_-8.jpg 1280w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) calc(100vw - 40px), 640px" /></p>
<p>It&#8217;s that time of year again. And that only means one thing: time to start thinking about the holiday baking. In Paris, bakery windows fill up with Bûches de Noël (Yule log cakes) and <em>bourriches</em> (wooden crates) of oysters are piled up at the markets. The chocolate shops are crammed with people, buying multiple boxes as gifts, and people splurge on caviar and Champagne, one of the few things that go on sale in France during the holidays.</p>
<p>One thing you don&#8217;t see is the use of pumpkin in desserts. A tart or pie (or <a href="https://www.davidlebovitz.com/pumpkin-ice-cream-recipe/">ice cream</a>) made of squash might sound funny, especially to non-Americans, but helps to remember that pumpkins, and other squash, are technically fruit. One could also point out the classic <a href="https://www.davidlebovitz.com/swiss-chard-tart-recipe-tourte-de-blettes/">Swiss Chard Tart</a> from Provence (which is in a whole other category), and <a href="http://memoriediangelina.com/2017/08/12/chocolate-eggplant/#.WeWgXBOCxE4">Melanzane al cioccolato</a>, eggplant with chocolate sauce, which I like. (Which one could argue is good because it&#8217;s smothered in dark chocolate.) But I don&#8217;t think everything goes with chocolate: A friend tried the hot chocolate with oysters at a famed chocolate shop in Paris, and after her description, I wasn&#8217;t rushing over there to try a cup.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-38352" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%20640%20829'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="" width="640" height="829" data-lazy-srcset="https://www.davidlebovitz.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Pumpkin-cheesecake-recipe-with-toffee-pecan-sauce_-640x829.jpg 640w, https://www.davidlebovitz.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Pumpkin-cheesecake-recipe-with-toffee-pecan-sauce_-232x300.jpg 232w, https://www.davidlebovitz.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Pumpkin-cheesecake-recipe-with-toffee-pecan-sauce_-768x994.jpg 768w, https://www.davidlebovitz.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Pumpkin-cheesecake-recipe-with-toffee-pecan-sauce_-150x194.jpg 150w, https://www.davidlebovitz.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Pumpkin-cheesecake-recipe-with-toffee-pecan-sauce_-600x777.jpg 600w, https://www.davidlebovitz.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Pumpkin-cheesecake-recipe-with-toffee-pecan-sauce_.jpg 1280w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 680px) calc(100vw - 40px), 640px" data-lazy-src="https://www.davidlebovitz.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Pumpkin-cheesecake-recipe-with-toffee-pecan-sauce_-640x829.jpg" /><noscript><img decoding="async" class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-38352" src="https://www.davidlebovitz.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Pumpkin-cheesecake-recipe-with-toffee-pecan-sauce_-640x829.jpg" alt="" width="640" height="829" srcset="https://www.davidlebovitz.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Pumpkin-cheesecake-recipe-with-toffee-pecan-sauce_-640x829.jpg 640w, https://www.davidlebovitz.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Pumpkin-cheesecake-recipe-with-toffee-pecan-sauce_-232x300.jpg 232w, https://www.davidlebovitz.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Pumpkin-cheesecake-recipe-with-toffee-pecan-sauce_-768x994.jpg 768w, https://www.davidlebovitz.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Pumpkin-cheesecake-recipe-with-toffee-pecan-sauce_-150x194.jpg 150w, https://www.davidlebovitz.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Pumpkin-cheesecake-recipe-with-toffee-pecan-sauce_-600x777.jpg 600w, https://www.davidlebovitz.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Pumpkin-cheesecake-recipe-with-toffee-pecan-sauce_.jpg 1280w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) calc(100vw - 40px), 640px" /></noscript></p>
<p>To get that last image out of your mind, I present <strong>pumpkin cheesecake with a pecan praline sauce</strong>, that has nothing <em>not</em> to like about it. Cream cheese and sour cream, a buttery cookie crust, and a brown sugar and bourbon-tinged sauce loaded with crunchy pecans. I&#8217;m in.</p>
<p><span id="more-38344"></span></p>
<p><img decoding="async" class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-38347" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%20640%20895'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="" width="640" height="895" data-lazy-srcset="https://www.davidlebovitz.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Pumpkin-cheesecake-recipe-with-toffee-pecan-sauce_-4-640x895.jpg 640w, https://www.davidlebovitz.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Pumpkin-cheesecake-recipe-with-toffee-pecan-sauce_-4-215x300.jpg 215w, https://www.davidlebovitz.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Pumpkin-cheesecake-recipe-with-toffee-pecan-sauce_-4-768x1074.jpg 768w, https://www.davidlebovitz.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Pumpkin-cheesecake-recipe-with-toffee-pecan-sauce_-4-150x210.jpg 150w, https://www.davidlebovitz.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Pumpkin-cheesecake-recipe-with-toffee-pecan-sauce_-4-600x839.jpg 600w, https://www.davidlebovitz.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Pumpkin-cheesecake-recipe-with-toffee-pecan-sauce_-4.jpg 1280w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 680px) calc(100vw - 40px), 640px" data-lazy-src="https://www.davidlebovitz.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Pumpkin-cheesecake-recipe-with-toffee-pecan-sauce_-4-640x895.jpg" /><noscript><img decoding="async" class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-38347" src="https://www.davidlebovitz.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Pumpkin-cheesecake-recipe-with-toffee-pecan-sauce_-4-640x895.jpg" alt="" width="640" height="895" srcset="https://www.davidlebovitz.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Pumpkin-cheesecake-recipe-with-toffee-pecan-sauce_-4-640x895.jpg 640w, https://www.davidlebovitz.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Pumpkin-cheesecake-recipe-with-toffee-pecan-sauce_-4-215x300.jpg 215w, https://www.davidlebovitz.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Pumpkin-cheesecake-recipe-with-toffee-pecan-sauce_-4-768x1074.jpg 768w, https://www.davidlebovitz.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Pumpkin-cheesecake-recipe-with-toffee-pecan-sauce_-4-150x210.jpg 150w, https://www.davidlebovitz.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Pumpkin-cheesecake-recipe-with-toffee-pecan-sauce_-4-600x839.jpg 600w, https://www.davidlebovitz.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Pumpkin-cheesecake-recipe-with-toffee-pecan-sauce_-4.jpg 1280w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) calc(100vw - 40px), 640px" /></noscript></p>
<p>DIYers may raise an eyebrow at using canned pumpkin. I&#8217;ve got a few reasons for using it. (And as many of you perhaps know, <a href="https://www.epicurious.com/ingredients/what-is-in-canned-pumpkin-article">it&#8217;s not made from pumpkin</a>, but a variety of squash similar to butternut squash.) One, is that when writing a recipe, it&#8217;s easy to get consistent, similar results when we&#8217;re all using the same ingredient. And two, it&#8217;s a heckuva lot easier, which is appreciated around the holidays when all of us have enough on our plates, and in our ovens, and it&#8217;s  fewer dishes to wash to boot.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-38345" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%20640%20859'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="" width="640" height="859" data-lazy-srcset="https://www.davidlebovitz.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Pumpkin-cheesecake-recipe-with-toffee-pecan-sauce_-2-640x859.jpg 640w, https://www.davidlebovitz.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Pumpkin-cheesecake-recipe-with-toffee-pecan-sauce_-2-224x300.jpg 224w, https://www.davidlebovitz.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Pumpkin-cheesecake-recipe-with-toffee-pecan-sauce_-2-768x1031.jpg 768w, https://www.davidlebovitz.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Pumpkin-cheesecake-recipe-with-toffee-pecan-sauce_-2-150x201.jpg 150w, https://www.davidlebovitz.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Pumpkin-cheesecake-recipe-with-toffee-pecan-sauce_-2-600x805.jpg 600w, https://www.davidlebovitz.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Pumpkin-cheesecake-recipe-with-toffee-pecan-sauce_-2.jpg 1280w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 680px) calc(100vw - 40px), 640px" data-lazy-src="https://www.davidlebovitz.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Pumpkin-cheesecake-recipe-with-toffee-pecan-sauce_-2-640x859.jpg" /><noscript><img decoding="async" class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-38345" src="https://www.davidlebovitz.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Pumpkin-cheesecake-recipe-with-toffee-pecan-sauce_-2-640x859.jpg" alt="" width="640" height="859" srcset="https://www.davidlebovitz.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Pumpkin-cheesecake-recipe-with-toffee-pecan-sauce_-2-640x859.jpg 640w, https://www.davidlebovitz.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Pumpkin-cheesecake-recipe-with-toffee-pecan-sauce_-2-224x300.jpg 224w, https://www.davidlebovitz.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Pumpkin-cheesecake-recipe-with-toffee-pecan-sauce_-2-768x1031.jpg 768w, https://www.davidlebovitz.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Pumpkin-cheesecake-recipe-with-toffee-pecan-sauce_-2-150x201.jpg 150w, https://www.davidlebovitz.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Pumpkin-cheesecake-recipe-with-toffee-pecan-sauce_-2-600x805.jpg 600w, https://www.davidlebovitz.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Pumpkin-cheesecake-recipe-with-toffee-pecan-sauce_-2.jpg 1280w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) calc(100vw - 40px), 640px" /></noscript></p>
<p>If you want to go the other route, you can also make your own <a href="https://www.culturesforhealth.com/learn/cheese/homemade-cream-cheese/">cream cheese</a> and <a href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2009/05/graham-crackers/">Graham crackers</a>, <a href="http://www.nola.com/homegarden/index.ssf/2014/12/how_to_grow_your_own_pecans_pl.html">grow your own pecans</a>, churn up your own <a href="https://www.theguardian.com/lifeandstyle/2010/feb/24/how-to-make-butter">butter</a>, and <a href="http://www.lindsayannbakes.com/2014/09/video-diy-disposable-baking-pans-heart.html">make your own cake pan</a>. If you do go that route, let me know when your cheesecake is done ; )</p>
<p><img decoding="async" class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-38346" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%20640%20829'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="" width="640" height="829" data-lazy-srcset="https://www.davidlebovitz.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Pumpkin-cheesecake-recipe-with-toffee-pecan-sauce_-3-640x829.jpg 640w, https://www.davidlebovitz.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Pumpkin-cheesecake-recipe-with-toffee-pecan-sauce_-3-232x300.jpg 232w, https://www.davidlebovitz.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Pumpkin-cheesecake-recipe-with-toffee-pecan-sauce_-3-768x994.jpg 768w, https://www.davidlebovitz.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Pumpkin-cheesecake-recipe-with-toffee-pecan-sauce_-3-150x194.jpg 150w, https://www.davidlebovitz.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Pumpkin-cheesecake-recipe-with-toffee-pecan-sauce_-3-600x777.jpg 600w, https://www.davidlebovitz.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Pumpkin-cheesecake-recipe-with-toffee-pecan-sauce_-3.jpg 1280w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 680px) calc(100vw - 40px), 640px" data-lazy-src="https://www.davidlebovitz.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Pumpkin-cheesecake-recipe-with-toffee-pecan-sauce_-3-640x829.jpg" /><noscript><img decoding="async" class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-38346" src="https://www.davidlebovitz.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Pumpkin-cheesecake-recipe-with-toffee-pecan-sauce_-3-640x829.jpg" alt="" width="640" height="829" srcset="https://www.davidlebovitz.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Pumpkin-cheesecake-recipe-with-toffee-pecan-sauce_-3-640x829.jpg 640w, https://www.davidlebovitz.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Pumpkin-cheesecake-recipe-with-toffee-pecan-sauce_-3-232x300.jpg 232w, https://www.davidlebovitz.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Pumpkin-cheesecake-recipe-with-toffee-pecan-sauce_-3-768x994.jpg 768w, https://www.davidlebovitz.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Pumpkin-cheesecake-recipe-with-toffee-pecan-sauce_-3-150x194.jpg 150w, https://www.davidlebovitz.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Pumpkin-cheesecake-recipe-with-toffee-pecan-sauce_-3-600x777.jpg 600w, https://www.davidlebovitz.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Pumpkin-cheesecake-recipe-with-toffee-pecan-sauce_-3.jpg 1280w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) calc(100vw - 40px), 640px" /></noscript></p>
<p>In the meantime, I&#8217;m standing over my stove, stirring warm, just-toasted pecans into my praline sauce before lacing it with a dash of bourbon.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-38348" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%20640%20906'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="" width="640" height="906" data-lazy-srcset="https://www.davidlebovitz.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Pumpkin-cheesecake-recipe-with-toffee-pecan-sauce_-5-640x906.jpg 640w, https://www.davidlebovitz.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Pumpkin-cheesecake-recipe-with-toffee-pecan-sauce_-5-212x300.jpg 212w, https://www.davidlebovitz.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Pumpkin-cheesecake-recipe-with-toffee-pecan-sauce_-5-768x1087.jpg 768w, https://www.davidlebovitz.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Pumpkin-cheesecake-recipe-with-toffee-pecan-sauce_-5-150x212.jpg 150w, https://www.davidlebovitz.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Pumpkin-cheesecake-recipe-with-toffee-pecan-sauce_-5-600x849.jpg 600w, https://www.davidlebovitz.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Pumpkin-cheesecake-recipe-with-toffee-pecan-sauce_-5.jpg 1280w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 680px) calc(100vw - 40px), 640px" data-lazy-src="https://www.davidlebovitz.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Pumpkin-cheesecake-recipe-with-toffee-pecan-sauce_-5-640x906.jpg" /><noscript><img decoding="async" class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-38348" src="https://www.davidlebovitz.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Pumpkin-cheesecake-recipe-with-toffee-pecan-sauce_-5-640x906.jpg" alt="" width="640" height="906" srcset="https://www.davidlebovitz.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Pumpkin-cheesecake-recipe-with-toffee-pecan-sauce_-5-640x906.jpg 640w, https://www.davidlebovitz.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Pumpkin-cheesecake-recipe-with-toffee-pecan-sauce_-5-212x300.jpg 212w, https://www.davidlebovitz.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Pumpkin-cheesecake-recipe-with-toffee-pecan-sauce_-5-768x1087.jpg 768w, https://www.davidlebovitz.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Pumpkin-cheesecake-recipe-with-toffee-pecan-sauce_-5-150x212.jpg 150w, https://www.davidlebovitz.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Pumpkin-cheesecake-recipe-with-toffee-pecan-sauce_-5-600x849.jpg 600w, https://www.davidlebovitz.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Pumpkin-cheesecake-recipe-with-toffee-pecan-sauce_-5.jpg 1280w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) calc(100vw - 40px), 640px" /></noscript></p>
<p>The praline sauce is decidedly on the sweet side. But that didn&#8217;t stop me (like, at all&#8230;) from dipping my spoon into it over and over and over again. Be sure to toast the pecans before using them. My pet-peeve in restaurants is when they don&#8217;t toast nuts. Toasting any nut usually improves it by at least 99%, if not more, so if you&#8217;re not consistently toasting your nuts before using them on salads, sauces, and in ice creams, start doing it now. It&#8217;s not too late.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-38349" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%20640%20888'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="" width="640" height="888" data-lazy-srcset="https://www.davidlebovitz.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Pumpkin-cheesecake-recipe-with-toffee-pecan-sauce_-6-640x888.jpg 640w, https://www.davidlebovitz.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Pumpkin-cheesecake-recipe-with-toffee-pecan-sauce_-6-216x300.jpg 216w, https://www.davidlebovitz.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Pumpkin-cheesecake-recipe-with-toffee-pecan-sauce_-6-768x1066.jpg 768w, https://www.davidlebovitz.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Pumpkin-cheesecake-recipe-with-toffee-pecan-sauce_-6-150x208.jpg 150w, https://www.davidlebovitz.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Pumpkin-cheesecake-recipe-with-toffee-pecan-sauce_-6-600x833.jpg 600w, https://www.davidlebovitz.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Pumpkin-cheesecake-recipe-with-toffee-pecan-sauce_-6.jpg 1280w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 680px) calc(100vw - 40px), 640px" data-lazy-src="https://www.davidlebovitz.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Pumpkin-cheesecake-recipe-with-toffee-pecan-sauce_-6-640x888.jpg" /><noscript><img decoding="async" class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-38349" src="https://www.davidlebovitz.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Pumpkin-cheesecake-recipe-with-toffee-pecan-sauce_-6-640x888.jpg" alt="" width="640" height="888" srcset="https://www.davidlebovitz.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Pumpkin-cheesecake-recipe-with-toffee-pecan-sauce_-6-640x888.jpg 640w, https://www.davidlebovitz.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Pumpkin-cheesecake-recipe-with-toffee-pecan-sauce_-6-216x300.jpg 216w, https://www.davidlebovitz.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Pumpkin-cheesecake-recipe-with-toffee-pecan-sauce_-6-768x1066.jpg 768w, https://www.davidlebovitz.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Pumpkin-cheesecake-recipe-with-toffee-pecan-sauce_-6-150x208.jpg 150w, https://www.davidlebovitz.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Pumpkin-cheesecake-recipe-with-toffee-pecan-sauce_-6-600x833.jpg 600w, https://www.davidlebovitz.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Pumpkin-cheesecake-recipe-with-toffee-pecan-sauce_-6.jpg 1280w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) calc(100vw - 40px), 640px" /></noscript></p>
<p>But I can&#8217;t imagine this cheesecake being served without it. Although I could imagine eating the sauce without the cheesecake. And if you&#8217;re anything like me, you might find yourself spooning it over ice cream, ladling it over <a href="https://www.davidlebovitz.com/pumpkin-pie-recipe-with-toasted-marshmallow-topping/">pumpkin pie</a> (without the marshmallow topping), or even spooning it right into your mouth, like I do.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-38350" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%20640%20394'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="" width="640" height="394" data-lazy-srcset="https://www.davidlebovitz.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Pumpkin-cheesecake-recipe-with-toffee-pecan-sauce_-7-640x394.jpg 640w, https://www.davidlebovitz.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Pumpkin-cheesecake-recipe-with-toffee-pecan-sauce_-7-300x185.jpg 300w, https://www.davidlebovitz.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Pumpkin-cheesecake-recipe-with-toffee-pecan-sauce_-7-768x473.jpg 768w, https://www.davidlebovitz.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Pumpkin-cheesecake-recipe-with-toffee-pecan-sauce_-7-150x92.jpg 150w, https://www.davidlebovitz.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Pumpkin-cheesecake-recipe-with-toffee-pecan-sauce_-7-600x370.jpg 600w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 680px) calc(100vw - 40px), 640px" data-lazy-src="https://www.davidlebovitz.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Pumpkin-cheesecake-recipe-with-toffee-pecan-sauce_-7-640x394.jpg" /><noscript><img decoding="async" class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-38350" src="https://www.davidlebovitz.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Pumpkin-cheesecake-recipe-with-toffee-pecan-sauce_-7-640x394.jpg" alt="" width="640" height="394" srcset="https://www.davidlebovitz.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Pumpkin-cheesecake-recipe-with-toffee-pecan-sauce_-7-640x394.jpg 640w, https://www.davidlebovitz.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Pumpkin-cheesecake-recipe-with-toffee-pecan-sauce_-7-300x185.jpg 300w, https://www.davidlebovitz.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Pumpkin-cheesecake-recipe-with-toffee-pecan-sauce_-7-768x473.jpg 768w, https://www.davidlebovitz.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Pumpkin-cheesecake-recipe-with-toffee-pecan-sauce_-7-150x92.jpg 150w, https://www.davidlebovitz.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Pumpkin-cheesecake-recipe-with-toffee-pecan-sauce_-7-600x370.jpg 600w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) calc(100vw - 40px), 640px" /></noscript></p>
<div id="recipe"></div><div id="wprm-recipe-container-52291" class="wprm-recipe-container" data-recipe-id="52291" data-servings="12"><div class="wprm-recipe wprm-recipe-template-dl-recipe-maker-1"><div class="wprm-container-float-right">
<div class="wprm-align-right"><a href="https://www.davidlebovitz.com/wprm_print/pumpkin-cheesecake-with-pecan-praline-sauce" style="color: #333333;" class="wprm-recipe-print wprm-recipe-link wprm-print-recipe-shortcode wprm-block-text-normal" data-recipe-id="52291" data-template="" target="_blank" rel="nofollow"><span class="wprm-recipe-icon wprm-recipe-print-icon"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" x="0px" y="0px" width="16px" height="16px" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><g ><path fill="#1b6f1b" d="M19,5.09V1c0-0.552-0.448-1-1-1H6C5.448,0,5,0.448,5,1v4.09C2.167,5.569,0,8.033,0,11v7c0,0.552,0.448,1,1,1h4v4c0,0.552,0.448,1,1,1h12c0.552,0,1-0.448,1-1v-4h4c0.552,0,1-0.448,1-1v-7C24,8.033,21.833,5.569,19,5.09z M7,2h10v3H7V2z M17,22H7v-9h10V22z M18,10c-0.552,0-1-0.448-1-1c0-0.552,0.448-1,1-1s1,0.448,1,1C19,9.552,18.552,10,18,10z"/></g></svg></span> Print</a>
</div>

